\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The output provided is just a list of workflow steps, not the requested final evaluation report.\\n- The task requires a consolidated evaluation report in Markdown format.\\n- The result must be returned as a Python list of strings, each string representing a Markdown element or paragraph.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n[\\n\\\"# Final Evaluation Report\\\",\\n\\\"\\\",\\n\\\"## 1. Job Requirements Summary\\\",\\n\\\"- **Position:** Senior Software Engineer\\\",\\n\\\"- **Key Skills:** Python, AWS, RESTful APIs, Microservices\\\",\\n\\\"- **Experience:** 5+ years in backend development\\\",\\n\\\"- **Education:** Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field\\\",\\n\\\"\\\",\\n\\\"## 2. Candidate Profile\\\",\\n\\\"- **Name:** John Doe\\\",\\n\\\"- **Total Experience:** 6 years\\\",\\n\\\"- **Education:** B.Sc. in Computer Science, University X\\\",\\n\\\"- **Technical Skills:** Python (6 yrs), Java (4 yrs), AWS (3 yrs), Docker & Kubernetes\\\",\\n\\\"- **Certifications:** AWS Certified Solutions Architect\\\",\\n\\\"\\\",\\n\\\"## 3. Interview Assessment & Scores\\\",\\n\\\"| Criterion               | Score (out of 10) | Notes                                                            |\\\",\\n\\\"|-------------------------|------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|\\\",\\n\\\"| Technical Knowledge     | 8                | Strong Python foundations; good AWS architecture understanding   |\\\",\\n\\\"| Problem Solving         | 7                | Approached design challenge methodically, minor edge-case misses |\\\",\\n\\\"| Code Quality            | 9                | Clear, maintainable code; proper use of design patterns          |\\\",\\n\\\"| Communication           | 9                | Articulate explanations; concise responses                      |\\\",\\n\\\"| Cultural Fit & Behavior | 7                | Collaborative attitude; could provide more examples of leadership|\\\",\\n\\\"\\\",\\n\\\"## 4. Strengths\\\",\\n\\\"- Deep expertise in Python and backend frameworks\\\",\\n\\\"- Solid AWS and cloud architecture experience\\\",\\n\\\"- Clear and structured communication style\\\",\\n\\\"\\\",\\n\\\"## 5. Areas for Improvement\\\",\\n\\\"- Expand knowledge of frontend frameworks for full-stack versatility\\\",\\n\\\"- Provide more detailed examples of leadership or mentorship roles\\\",\\n\\\"\\\",\\n\\\"## 6. Overall Recommendation\\\",\\n\\\"Proceed to final offer stage pending reference checks. Candidate demonstrates strong technical skills, effective communication, and aligns well with team culture.\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a Python list of strings.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Implement parser to extract key requirements from the job description\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"job_description\\\": \\\"<paste the full job description text here>\\\",\\n  \\\"extracted_requirements\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"<e.g. Software Engineer>\\\",\\n    \\\"company\\\": \\\"<e.g. Google>\\\",\\n    \\\"required_skills\\\": [\\n      \\\"<e.g. Java>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Python>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Data Structures>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Algorithms>\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"minimum_experience\\\": \\\"<e.g. 2+ years of software development experience>\\\",\\n    \\\"education\\\": \\\"<e.g. Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field>\\\",\\n    \\\"key_responsibilities\\\": [\\n      \\\"<e.g. Design, develop, test, and deploy software solutions>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define and deliver features>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Participate in code reviews>\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"nice_to_have\\\": [\\n      \\\"<e.g. Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP)>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Knowledge of machine learning principles>\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"benefits\\\": [\\n      \\\"<e.g. Competitive salary>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Health insurance>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Paid time off>\\\",\\n      \\\"<e.g. Stock options>\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"location\\\": \\\"<e.g. Mountain View, CA>\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Implement parser to extract candidate information from the resume\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"name\\\": {\\n    \\\"first\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"last\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"contact_information\\\": {\\n    \\\"email\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"phone\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"address\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"education\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"institution\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"degree\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\",\\n      \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"work_experience\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"company\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\",\\n      \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\",\\n      \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n        \\\"string\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"skills\\\": [\\n    \\\"string\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"projects\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"technologies\\\": [\\n        \\\"string\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"link\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"publications\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"conference\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"awards_and_certifications\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"volunteer_experience\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"organization\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"role\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\",\\n      \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"string (YYYY-MM)\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"languages\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"language\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"proficiency\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"references\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"relation\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"email\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"phone\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Implement scoring engine to evaluate and score captured candidate responses\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport json\\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Tuple\\n\\nclass ScoringEngine:\\n    def __init__(self,\\n                 rubric: Dict[str, Dict[str, int]],\\n                 weights: Dict[str, float],\\n                 scale_min: float = 0.0,\\n                 scale_max: float = 100.0):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        rubric: {\\n          question_id: { \\\"Excellent\\\":5, \\\"Good\\\":3, \\\"Fair\\\":2, \\\"Poor\\\":1 },\\n          ...\\n        }\\n        weights: {\\n          question_id: weight_value (sum should be 1.0),\\n          ...\\n        }\\n        scale_min, scale_max: normalization range\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.rubric = rubric\\n        self.weights = weights\\n        self.scale_min = scale_min\\n        self.scale_max = scale_max\\n        self.raw_scores: Dict[str, float] = {}\\n        self.rationales: Dict[str, str] = {}\\n    \\n    def score_response(self, question_id: str, response: str) -> Tuple[float, str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Stub scoring: choose level based on keyword counts. Replace with NLP logic as needed.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        levels = self.rubric.get(question_id, {})\\n        # Simple keyword-based assignment for demo\\n        resp_lower = response.lower()\\n        if \\\"excellent\\\" in resp_lower or len(resp_lower) > 200:\\n            level = \\\"Excellent\\\"\\n        elif \\\"good\\\" in resp_lower or len(resp_lower) > 100:\\n            level = \\\"Good\\\"\\n        elif \\\"fair\\\" in resp_lower or len(resp_lower) > 50:\\n            level = \\\"Fair\\\"\\n        else:\\n            level = \\\"Poor\\\"\\n        \\n        score = levels.get(level, 0)\\n        rationale = f\\\"Matched level '{level}' -> score {score}\\\"\\n        return score, rationale\\n\\n    def score_candidate(self, responses: Dict[str, str]) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        responses: { question_id: candidate_response, ... }\\n        Fills self.raw_scores and self.rationales\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for qid, resp in responses.items():\\n            score, rationale = self.score_response(qid, resp)\\n            self.raw_scores[qid] = score\\n            self.rationales[qid] = rationale\\n\\n    def normalize_scores(self) -> Dict[str, float]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Normalizes raw_scores to [scale_min, scale_max].\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        max_raw = max(self.raw_scores.values(), default=0)\\n        min_raw = min(self.raw_scores.values(), default=0)\\n        normed: Dict[str, float] = {}\\n        for qid, raw in self.raw_scores.items():\\n            if max_raw == min_raw:\\n                norm = (self.scale_max + self.scale_min) / 2.0\\n            else:\\n                norm = ((raw - min_raw) / (max_raw - min_raw)) * (self.scale_max - self.scale_min) + self.scale_min\\n            normed[qid] = round(norm, 2)\\n        return normed\\n\\n    def overall_score(self, normalized_scores: Dict[str, float]) -> float:\\n        total = 0.0\\n        for qid, score in normalized_scores.items():\\n            weight = self.weights.get(qid, 0)\\n            total += score * weight\\n        return round(total, 2)\\n\\n    def adjust_score(self, question_id: str, new_score: float) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Manual override for a question's raw score.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.raw_scores[question_id] = new_score\\n        self.rationales[question_id] = f\\\"Manually adjusted to {new_score}\\\"\\n\\n    def generate_report(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns a structured report.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        normalized = self.normalize_scores()\\n        report = {\\n            \\\"raw_scores\\\": self.raw_scores,\\n            \\\"rationales\\\": self.rationales,\\n            \\\"normalized_scores\\\": normalized,\\n            \\\"overall_score\\\": self.overall_score(normalized)\\n        }\\n        return report\\n\\n    def save_scores(self, filepath: str) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Securely store scores. Here we JSON-dump; replace with secure storage as needed.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        with open(filepath, \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n            json.dump(self.generate_report(), f, indent=2)\\n\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Define a sample rubric and weights\\n    rubric = {\\n        \\\"Q1\\\": {\\\"Excellent\\\": 5, \\\"Good\\\": 3, \\\"Fair\\\": 2, \\\"Poor\\\": 1},\\n        \\\"Q2\\\": {\\\"Excellent\\\": 4, \\\"Good\\\": 3, \\\"Fair\\\": 2, \\\"Poor\\\": 1},\\n        \\\"Q3\\\": {\\\"Excellent\\\": 3, \\\"Good\\\": 2, \\\"Fair\\\": 1, \\\"Poor\\\": 0},\\n    }\\n    weights = {\\\"Q1\\\": 0.5, \\\"Q2\\\": 0.3, \\\"Q3\\\": 0.2}\\n\\n    # Sample candidate responses\\n    candidate_responses = {\\n        \\\"Q1\\\": \\\"I have extensive experience and I believe my work was excellent.\\\",\\n        \\\"Q2\\\": \\\"My performance was good and I met all objectives.\\\",\\n        \\\"Q3\\\": \\\"I did fair work but there is room for improvement.\\\"\\n    }\\n\\n    engine = ScoringEngine(rubric, weights)\\n    engine.score_candidate(candidate_responses)\\n    # Optional manual adjust\\n    # engine.adjust_score(\\\"Q3\\\", 2.5)\\n    report = engine.generate_report()\\n    print(json.dumps(report, indent=2))\\n```\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nGenerate final evaluation report consolidating requirement analysis, resume data, and scores\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nMarkdown\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\n[\\n    \\\"# Final Evaluation Report\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"## 1. Job Requirements Summary\\\",\\n    \\\"Job requirements are parsed from the job description in Task task0.\\\",\\n    \\\"The extracted information includes:\\\",\\n    \\\"- Job Title: <job_title>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Company: <company>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Required Skills: <required_skills>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Minimum Experience: <minimum_experience>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Education: <education>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Key Responsibilities: <key_responsibilities>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Nice-to-have Skills: <nice_to_have>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Benefits: <benefits>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Location: <location>\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"## 2. Candidate Profile\\\",\\n    \\\"Candidate information is extracted from the resume in Task task1.\\\",\\n    \\\"The extracted information includes:\\\",\\n    \\\"- Name: <first_name> <last_name>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Contact Information: <email>, <phone>, <address>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Education: <education_details>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Work Experience: <work_experience_details>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Skills: <skills_list>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Projects: <projects_list>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Publications: <publications_list>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Awards and Certifications: <awards_and_certifications_list>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Volunteer Experience: <volunteer_experience_list>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Languages: <languages_list>\\\",\\n    \\\"- References: Available upon request\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"## 3. Interview Assessment & Scores\\\",\\n    \\\"Candidate responses are scored using the scoring engine in Task task4.\\\",\\n    \\\"The scoring rubric and weights are defined in the ScoringEngine class.\\\",\\n    \\\"The overall score is calculated based on normalized scores and assigned weights.\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"**Scoring Details:**\\\",\\n    \\\"- Raw Scores: <raw_scores>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Rationales: <rationales>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Normalized Scores: <normalized_scores>\\\",\\n    \\\"- Overall Score: <overall_score>\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"## 4. Summary\\\",\\n    \\\"This report consolidates job requirements, candidate profile, and interview scores to provide a comprehensive evaluation.\\\",\\n    \\\"The information is used to assess the candidate's suitability for the job.\\\"\\n]\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T12:08:06.613484\"\n}"}
